  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypertensive disorders of pregnancy are one of the most frequent complications of pregnancy,
      being a serious health problem around the world.

      Previous studies have suggested that there is an association between a short period of
      exposure to paternal sperm of a new sexual partner and the development of an immunological
      reaction that could trigger a hypertensive disorder of pregnancy. For this reason we want to
      study the relationship between the primipaternity concept (exposure to male antigens present
      in semen over a short period of time previous to the pregnancy) and the development of
      preeclampsia in adolescents.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
